ves%20in%20criminal%20trials.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnicolas-maduro-manhattan-court-charges-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENicol%C3%A1s%20Maduro%3C%2Fa%3E%20needed%20someone%20to%20represent%20him%20in%20an%20American%20courtroom%2C%20he%20turned%20to%20a%20lawyer%20with%20experience%20facing%20off%20against%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flatest-us-captures-venezuela-president-nicolas-maduro-strikes-caracas-trump-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVenezuelan%20political%20leader%3C%2Fa%3E%20hired%20Barry%20Pollack%2C%20a%20criminal%20defense%20attorney%20who's%20represented%20WikiLeaks%20publisher%20Julian%20Assange%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20high-profile%20defendants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20has%20accused%20Maduro%2C%20who%20was%20serving%20as%20Venezuela's%20president%20when%20he%20was%20captured%20by%20US%20forces%2C%20of%20participating%20in%20a%20narco-terrorism%20conspiracy%2C%20alleging%20he%20worked%20with%20illegal%20drug%20gangs.%20They%20also%20accused%20him%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Cilia%20Flores%2C%20of%20conspiring%20to%20illegally%20import%20cocaine%20into%20the%20United%20States%20and%20of%20gun-related%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%20afternoon%2C%20US%20Marshals%20escorted%20the%20couple%20into%20a%2026th-floor%20courtroom%20in%20lower%20Manhattan%2C%20where%20they%20entered%20not-guilty%20pleas%20and%20proclaimed%20their%20innocence.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideos-shows-venezuelan-president-nicolas-maduro-arriving-in-new-york-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20military%20forces%20apprehended%20Maduro%20and%20Flores%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20pre-dawn%20operation%20on%20Saturday%20in%20the%20Venezuelan%20capital%20of%20Caracas%20and%20brought%20them%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20hearing%2C%20Pollack%20told%20US%20District%20Judge%20Alvin%20Hellerstein%20that%20he%20would%20file%20%26quot%3Bvoluminous%20and%20complicated%26quot%3B%20motions%20on%20Maduro's%20behalf%2C%20suggesting%20he%20would%20challenge%20the%20charges%20and%20the%20basis%20for%20his%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Maduro%20is%20the%20head%20of%20a%20sovereign%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Pollack%20said%20in%20court.%20%26quot%3BHe%20is%20entitled%20to%20the%20privileges%20and%20immunities%20that%20go%20with%20that%20office.%20In%20addition%2C%20there%20are%20issues%20about%20the%20legality%20of%20this%20military%20abduction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDelcy%20Rodriguez%20was%20sworn%20in%20as%20Venezuela's%20interim%20president%20on%20Monday%20afternoon.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPollack%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20boutique%20law%20firm%20Harris%20St.%20Laurent%20%26amp%3B%20Wechsler%20LLP%2C%20is%20best%20known%20as%20one%20of%20the%20many%20lawyers%20who%20represented%20Assange%2C%20the%20publisher%20of%20WikiLeaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20had%20accused%20Assange%20of%20working%20with%20hackers%20to%20obtain%20government%20secrets%20from%20federal%20agencies%20and%20American%20companies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20conspiring%20with%20former%20US%20Army%20officer%20Chelsea%20Manning%20to%20leak%20documents%20about%20the%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAssange%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20espionage%20charges%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202024%2C%20capping%20a%20six-year%20legal%20battle%20that%20involved%20complex%20negotiations%20with%20multiple%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPollack's%20experience%20with%20sensitive%20national%20security%20matters%20could%20be%20an%20asset%20for%20his%20representation%20of%20Maduro%2C%20which%20will%20likely%20involve%20classified%20information.%20The%20attorney%20has%20also%20represented%20Jeffrey%20Sterling%2C%20a%20former%20CIA%20officer%20who%20was%20convicted%20of%20espionage%20charges%20after%20leaking%20information%20to%20a%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22barry%20pollack%20nicolas%20maduro%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F695c2f6f64858d02d217c62a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBarry%20Pollack%2C%20on%20the%20left%2C%20represented%20Maduro%20in%20Manhattan%20federal%20court%20on%20Monday%20afternoon.%3Cp%3EJane%20Rosenberg%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20paid%2C%20Pollack%20will%20likely%20need%20a%20waiver%20from%20the%20US%20Treasury%20Department%2C%20which%20has%20sanctioned%20Maduro%20and%20the%20Venezuelan%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20when%20Pollack%20began%20representing%20Maduro.%20He%20formally%20entered%20an%20appearance%20on%20the%20court%20docket%20late%20Monday%20morning.%20Maduro%20was%20first%20indicted%20in%202020%2C%20and%20Hellerstein%20has%20overseen%20court%20proceedings%20against%20other%20Venezuelan%20nationals%20accused%20of%20conspiring%20with%20him.%20Pollack%20didn't%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20court-appointed%20lawyer%20for%20Maduro%2C%20David%20Wikstrom%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20was%20informed%20at%208%3A40%20a.m.%20on%20Monday%20that%20he%20would%20be%20representing%20the%20Venezuelan%20president%20in%20court.%20Shortly%20before%20the%20noon%20court%20hearing%2C%20he%20said%20he%20still%20hadn't%20spoken%20to%20Pollack%2C%20who%20ultimately%20represented%20Maduro%20in%20the%20proceeding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlores%20is%20represented%20by%20Mark%20Donnelly%2C%20a%20Texas-based%20attorney%20who%20served%20as%20a%20federal%20prosecutor%20for%2012%20years%2C%20and%20one%20of%20his%20law%20partners%2C%20Andres%20Sanchez.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPollack%2C%20a%20former%20public%20defender%20and%20president%20of%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Criminal%20Defense%20Lawyers%2C%20has%20a%20long%20track%20record%20of%20successful%20defense%20outcomes%20in%20criminal%20trials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20represented%20former%20Enron%20accountant%20Michael%20W.%20Krautz%2C%20who%20a%20jury%20acquitted%20of%20fraud%20charges.%20And%20he%20successfully%20overturned%20the%20conviction%20of%20Martin%20Tankleff%2C%20a%20Long%20Island%20man%20who%20spent%2017%20years%20in%20prison%20after%20he%20was%20falsely%20accused%20of%20killing%20his%20parents%20as%20a%20teenager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20Pollack%20represented%20the%20executive%20of%20a%20poultry%20company%20accused%20of%20conspiring%20to%20fix%20the%20price%20of%20chickens.%20Jurors%20declined%20to%20find%20the%20executive%20guilty%20in%20two%20separate%20trials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lawdragon.com%2Flawyer-limelights%2F2025-04-03-defending-julian-assange-barry-pollack-on-the-historic-plea-deal-and-the-future-of-white-collar-defense%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202025%20interview%20with%20Lawdragon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Pollack%20decried%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%20view%26quot%3B%20of%20its%20jurisdiction%20for%20criminal%20cases%2C%20using%20the%20Assange%20case%20as%20an%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20somebody%20who's%20not%20a%20United%20States%20citizen%20who%20is%20publishing%20information%20not%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20had%20not%20set%20foot%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20with%20respect%20to%20any%20of%20the%20alleged%20offensive%20conduct%2C%26quot%3B%20Pollack%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20information%20was%20leaked%20to%20him%20by%20somebody%20in%20Iraq.%20Yet%20the%20United%20States%20obviously%20felt%20that%20it%20could%20pursue%20that%20as%20a%20criminal%20offense%20in%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarry-pollack-nicolas-maduros-lawyer-represented-julian-assange-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2F