0and%20his%20wife%2C%20Cilia%20Flores%2C%20appeared%20in%20a%20Manhattan%20court%20on%20drug-trafficking%20charges.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Venezuelan%20president%20and%20Flores%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%20the%20federal%20charges%20facing%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20forces%20captured%20the%20pair%20over%20the%20weekend%20during%20a%20military%20raid%20on%20Caracas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EVenezuelan%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flatest-us-captures-venezuela-president-nicolas-maduro-strikes-caracas-trump-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENicol%C3%A1s%20Maduro%3C%2Fa%3E%20defiantly%20proclaimed%20his%20innocence%20in%20a%20Manhattan%20federal%20court%20Monday%20morning%20during%20his%20and%20his%20wife's%20first%20public%20appearance%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideos-shows-venezuelan-president-nicolas-maduro-arriving-in-new-york-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20forces%20captured%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20dramatic%20military%20raid%20on%20Caracas%20over%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20innocent.%20I%20am%20not%20guilty.%20I%20am%20a%20decent%20man.%20I%20am%20still%20president%20of%20my%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Maduro%20told%20the%20judge%20through%20an%20interpreter%20when%20asked%20for%20his%20plea%20on%20narco-terrorism%20and%20weapons%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20then%20interrupted%20by%20the%20judge%2C%20who%20interjected%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20not%20guilty%20plea%20will%20be%20entered%20on%20behalf%20of%20Mr.%20Maduro.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20one%20of%20several%20dramatic%20moments%20during%20the%20roughly%2030-minute%20hearing%2C%20which%20Maduro%20used%20to%20protest%20his%20capture%20by%20US%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20entered%20the%20courtroom%2C%20flanked%20by%20US%20marshals%2C%20he%20wished%20everyone%20a%20%26quot%3BHappy%20New%20Year%26quot%3B%20in%20English%20and%20locked%20eyes%20with%20members%20of%20the%20press%20sitting%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20as%20the%20hearing%20wrapped%20up%2C%20a%20person%20sitting%20in%20the%20fourth%20row%20of%20the%20courtroom%20gallery%20stood%20to%20say%20Maduro%20would%20pay%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Venezuelan%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20a%20man%20of%20God%2C%20and%20I%20am%20a%20war%20prisoner%2C%26quot%3B%20Maduro%20responded%20in%20Spanish%20as%20US%20marshals%20escorted%20him%20out%20of%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaduro%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Cilia%20Flores%2C%20were%20arraigned%20on%20an%20indictment%20alleging%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20import%20cocaine%20and%20a%20related%20conspiracy%20to%20possess%20machine%20guns%20and%20other%20%26quot%3Bdestructive%20devices%26quot%3B%20in%20furtherance%20of%20drug%20trafficking.%20Maduro%20also%20faces%20a%20narco-terrorism%20conspiracy%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20wore%20standard-issue%20jail%20garb%20of%20navy%20smocks%20over%20orange%20long-sleeve%20shirts%20with%20khaki%20pants.%20At%20their%20seats%20in%20the%20courtroom%2C%20they%20wore%20headphones%20to%20listen%20to%20their%20court-appointed%20translators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20stood%20to%20address%20the%20judge%2C%20Maduro%20held%20on%20to%20the%20arms%20of%20his%20chair%20as%20he%20rose%20unsteadily.%20Flores%2C%20her%20blonde%20hair%20tied%20back%20in%20a%20bun%2C%20had%20several%20small%20bandages%20on%20her%20face.%20She%20sustained%20injuries%20during%20her%20%26quot%3Babduction%26quot%3B%20in%20Caracas%2C%20one%20of%20her%20attorneys%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20packed%20noon%20hearing%2C%20US%20District%20Judge%20Alvin%20Hellerstein%20read%20the%20couple%20a%20summary%20of%20their%20charges%20and%20informed%20the%20Venezuelan%20president%20and%20first%20lady%20of%20their%20rights%20before%20the%20pair%20entered%20not%20guilty%20pleas.%20He%20addressed%20them%20as%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Maduro%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BMs.%20Flores.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20to%20confirm%20his%20identity%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20Maduro%20began%20by%20stating%20in%20firmly%20spoken%20Spanish%20that%20he%20is%20%26quot%3BPresidente%20constitutional%20de%20la%20Republica%20Venezuela.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20here%2C%20kidnapped%2C%20since%20January%203%2C%20Saturday%2C%26quot%3B%20Maduro%20said.%20I%20was%20captured%20in%20my%20home%20in%20Caracas%2C%20Venezuela.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20a%20time%20and%20place%20to%20go%20into%20all%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20interrupted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20for%20her%20plea%2C%20Flores%20spoke%20in%20a%20quiet%2C%20hoarse%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20guilty.%20Completely%20innocent%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20through%20a%20court%20interpreter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Maduro%20and%20Flores%20are%20facing%20health%20issues%20and%20will%20need%20medical%20attention%20while%20awaiting%20trial%2C%20their%20lawyers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMiss%20Flores%2C%20during%20her%20abduction%2C%20sustained%20significant%20injuries%2C%20as%20you%20can%20see%20today%20here%20in%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20defense%20lawyer%20Mark%20Donnelly%20told%20the%20judge.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20belief%20that%20she%20may%20have%20a%20fracture%20or%20severe%20bruising%20on%20her%20ribs%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawyer%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2025-page%20indictment%20filed%20against%20Maduro%2C%20his%20wife%2C%20son%2C%20and%20three%20others%20alleges%20that%20for%20over%2025%20years%2C%20Venezuelan%20leaders%20%26quot%3Bhave%20abused%20their%20positions%20of%20public%20trust%20and%20corrupted%20once-legitimate%20institutions%20to%20import%20tons%20of%20cocaine%20into%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaduro%20was%20represented%20in%20court%20by%20Barry%20Pollack%2C%20an%20attorney%20best%20known%20for%20also%20representing%20WikiLeaks%20publisher%20Julian%20Assan